attributeList.attribute: INTerAction database (IntAct) provides an open source database and toolkit for the storage, presentation and analysis of molecular interactions.
European Bioinformatics Institute; Wellcome Trust Genome Campus; Hinxton, Cambridge; CB10 1SD; United Kingdom
A collection of literature-mined stable and functionally defined human molecular complexes of known stoichiometry and biological role.

names.alias: Small nuclear ribonucleoprotein D homolog SNP3

attributeList.attribute: The hetero-heptameric complex of seven Lsm proteins (Lsm2-8) affects the processing of small stable RNAs (including tRNAs, rRNAs) and pre-mRNAs in the nucleus. The complex is part of the U6 snRNA, where it binds to the U6 RNA and contributes to stabilizing the U6 snRNA and chaperoning it through the splicing process. The Lsm2-8 complex is thought to pre-exist in the cell and bind to U6 as a complex.
